      "message": "I wonder if we can avoid all the LenghtContext complications/changes if we resolve against a [0..1] length context and then post-scale to OBB?\n\nIIRC in blink we do something along these lines:\n\n  auto lctx \u003d fGradientUnits.type() \u003d\u003d SkSVGGradientUnits::Type::kObjectBoundingBox\n      ? SkSVGLength({1,1}) : ctx.lengthContext();\n\n  auto x1 \u003d lctx.resolve(fX1);\n  ...\n\n  if (fGradientUnits.type() \u003d\u003d SkSVGGradientUnits::Type::kObjectBoundingBox) {\n      // remap from unit space to object bounding box\n      x1 \u003d OBB.x() + OBB.width() * x1;\n      ...\n  }\n\nThen we don\u0027t need the length context to know about an offset/origin. WDYT?",
